<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">09, Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Washer repair, what people ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does washer repair cost?</h3>
        <p>Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair the moment you approve the work. Most washer repairs run between $130 and $350 depending on the part and brand. Drain pump and lid switch replacements are on the lower end. Control board, motor, or tub-bearing work on premium brands like Miele or Bosch run higher. We give you a full written estimate before any work begins, what we quote is what appears on the invoice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover?</h3>
        <p>All five counties: Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside. We dispatch from 8 service territories, West Hollywood (HQ), Los Angeles, Beverly Hills, Pasadena, Thousand Oaks, Irvine, Rancho Cucamonga, and Temecula, so the technician on your call is coming from the closest one. Same-day is our standard.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can you repair my washer the same day?</h3>
        <p>Yes. We have technicians running washer calls daily across all 5 SoCal counties. Call before noon and we can typically be there that afternoon. We stock parts for the brands we see most often, Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Miele, Bosch, so most repairs are completed on the first visit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair stackable washers in apartments and condos?</h3>
        <p>Yes, stackable units in closets and laundry alcoves are one of the most common washer calls we get. Working in a tight laundry closet requires a specific approach. Our technicians come prepared for it: the right tools, the right sequence for accessing components without damaging cabinetry, and experience with the brands commonly spec'd in SoCal condos, LG, Electrolux, Bosch, Samsung.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My front-load washer smells like mold, can you fix that?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Front-load washers in apartments and condos with limited ventilation are prone to mold buildup on the rubber door gasket. We clean the drum and gasket, inspect for tears or deterioration that trap water, and check whether the door seal needs replacement. We also look at the drain path to make sure residual water isn't sitting where it shouldn't be.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My washer won't drain, what's usually wrong?</h3>
        <p>The drain pump is the most common culprit, especially if you hear the motor running but water stays in the drum. It could also be a clogged pump filter, on front-loaders, this is the small access panel near the bottom front of the machine, and it's frequently neglected. A blocked drain hose, kinked outlet, or a faulty lid switch on top-loaders are also common. Our technicians diagnose before replacing parts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>When does it make sense to repair vs replace a washer?</h3>
        <p>Rule of thumb (the 50% rule): if the repair is less than half the cost of a comparable new machine, repair. If a $1,200 mid-market washer needs $700 in repairs and is over 8 years old, replace. Premium brands (Miele, Bosch, Speed Queen, Electrolux Professional) flip the math, they're built for 15-20 year service lives and worth repairing well past year 10. We tell you straight which side of the line your unit falls on.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does the 90-day warranty cover on washer repairs?</h3>
        <p>Our 90-day warranty covers both the part and the labor on every repair we complete. If the same issue returns within that period, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair high-efficiency (HE) and commercial washers?</h3>
        <p>Yes. High-efficiency front-load and top-load washers are the majority of what we service. For commercial washers, laundromat units, multi-family building machines, hotel laundry, our commercial diagnostic fee is $120. We work on Speed Queen, Electrolux Professional, Huebsch, and other commercial-grade brands.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

